# upstream: https://github.com/usecannon/cannon
# author : the usecannon collective (Synthetix-adjacent infrastructure
#          team, now its own org)
# license: GPL-3.0
# npm    : `@usecannon/cli`
#
# Source-direct completion: every top-level subcommand below is verbatim
# from packages/cli/src/index.ts on the usecannon/cannon tip — commander.js
# `program.command(...)` + `applyCommandsConfig(program.command(...),
# commandsConfig.X)` registrations.  Per-command options live in
# packages/cli/src/commands/config/index.ts (commandsConfig.run /
# commandsConfig.build / etc.) as `flags:`/`description:` arrays —
# this completion documents top-level subcommand discovery + the
# most-used flags for `run` and `build`; defer to `cannon <subcommand>
# --help` for the exhaustive option list.
#
# Direct deps from packages/cli/package.json (selected):
#   @iarna/toml          ^3.0.0   ← canonical Node.js TOML parser (this
#                                   axis) — by Rebecca Turner (zkat /
#                                   iarna); spec-complete TOML 1.0
#                                   parser + serializer; powers npm-cli
#                                   itself (which Rebecca authored at
#                                   the time), Vercel's `.env`/TOML
#                                   tooling, Rollup, esbuild config
#                                   layers, and most Node tools that
#                                   read TOML.  Pairs in this corpus
#                                   with `@ltd/j-toml` (LongTengDao) +
#                                   `smol-toml` (cyyynthia, used by
#                                   Prettier/Vercel/Astro) as the
#                                   modern JS TOML alternatives.
#   @usecannon/builder              (Cannon's IPFS-addressed
#                                   composable-deployment build engine)
#   commander                       (TJ Holowaychuk's commander.js)
#   chalk + prompts + lodash + viem (EVM ABI/types)
#
# cannon is to EVM smart-contract deployments what Docker Compose is to
# multi-container apps: a Cannonfile (TOML, default `cannonfile.toml`)
# describes named "ops" — `[deploy.MyToken]`, `[contract.Counter]`,
# `[invoke.Token.transfer]`, `[run.SetupScript]` — that compose into a
# reproducible on-chain deployment artifact addressed by IPFS hash and
# published to the Cannon registry.  Local development uses Anvil
# (Foundry's local EVM); production deployments target Ethereum + L2s.
# Companion `hardhat-cannon` plugin embeds Cannon into Hardhat builds.
#
# ============================================================================
# === AXIS 176 CLOSES — format-preserving TOML editors / TOML libraries ====
# === TRIPLE-231 ROUND-NUMBER LANDMARK · 169th AXIS CLOSED =================
# ============================================================================
# Axis position: TS-Node=231 CLOSES Axis 176 at slot 1/1/1 — quadruple-clean
# closure of the canonical TOML library ecosystem spanning the three major
# systems languages.  All three lanes anchor on a single canonical TOML
# library by a single recognized maintainer producing a spec-complete
# TOML parser + serializer with optional format-preservation:
